"NOT FOUND"|"pagus Tigurinus. See Geogr. Index. Pagus was the Roman name for the local divisions of German and Celtic tribes, which the Germans themselves called ***Hundreds,*** according to Tacitus (Germ. 6); perhaps as originally containing a hundred households. The word *** Hundred *** is still retained as the name of an English local division. The name for the district is here used of the men belonging to it. Cp. note on 37, 3."

