"NOT FOUND"|"cuniculus. ***A mine.*** Greek Mropos. The word cuniculus, originally a ***rabbit,*** was applied to a mine from the resemblance to the rabbit's burrow, multis locis. [N. S. V. G. 1, 137.] aerariae structurae. *** Mining works, *** aerariae being an adjective from aes, ***copper.*** There is another reading, aerariae structuraeque, in which case aerariae is a substantive *** copperworks,*** like ferrariae^ ironworks."

