"NOT FOUND"|"4. regnum. There was no monarchy in the usual sense of the word amongst the Gauls; regnum here means the despotic ascendancy which powerful chiefs often attained over their tribe, multos annos. [** 102.]obtinuerat. *** Had held.*** This is the proper meaning of obtinere, though it is not unfrequently used in the sense of its English derivative *** obtain,*** as below, in section 5 and in 18, 5."

