"NOT FOUND"|"Quodsi***voluisset. An answer to Ariovistus* claim of priority in Gaul, section 14 of the preceding chapter. The Romans had conquered two Gallic tribes in b.c. 121, and so had had the right of war to annex them; but they had judged it best to leave the Gauls free, and therefore opposed any attack on their liberty by others."

