"NOT FOUND"|"exisset. [** 149.]possent. [** 150.]et item***pueri. There is a sudden and ungrammatical change from the subordinate relative clauses (qni***qui) to a co-ordinate clause, coupled by ct. In strict grammar pueri, etc., should be genitives dependent on ratio; asjit is, a verb must be supplied to suit the sense from confecta estf e.g. conscripti sunt. *** In which list an account was drawn up of the number of those who had left their home, who were able to bear arms, and likewise the children, old men, and women (were entered) separately.***pueri, senes mulieresque. When three or more nouns stand side by side in the same grammatical construction, they are either (1) all connected by conjunctions; or (2) none; or-que is appended to the last, as here."

