"NOT FOUND"|"eo***minus. [N. S. V. R p. 137.] memoria. [** 112.] ferre. Without expressed subject (se). si alicujus. Aliquis is used for the indefinite quis after si and ne when the pronoun is emphatic =*** any whatever *** (Madvig, Lat. Or. 493, Ohs. 1). injuriae, [g 133.]fuisse. *** It was not;*** for fuit in oratio recta. deceptum. Perfect infinitive passive (esse omitted). *** But it had been deceived by the fact that it was neither conscious of any deed of its own which could cause it apprehension, and thought groundless apprehensions unworthy.*** timendum. [** 144.]contumeliae. [** 133, a.]quod eo invito***quod Aeduos, etc. This repetition of a word (quod) in the place of conjunctions is called anaphora. Cp. 19, 1; 43, 4."

