"NOT FOUND"|"Quod***dicantur. The present tense is probably intended to signify that the rumour of mutiny was still current, i.e. it is used of a present incompleted action, like traducat in 44, 12, q. v. laturi. [** 94.]fuerit. Perfect of a general, and therefore always present, truth. See note on 14, 4, velint.avaritiam esse convictam. Convincere aliquem, ***to prove a person guilty or wrong,*** is the usual construction ; but convincere aliquid alicui, ***to prove a thing*** (fault or crime) *** against a person,*** is also found."

