"caesar una aestate duobus maximis bellis confectis maturius paulo quam tempus anni postulabat in hiberna in sequanos exercitum deduxit; hibernis labienum praeposuit;  ipse in citeriorem galliam ad CONVENTUS Agendos profectus est."|"conventus. A Roman province was divided, for convenience of administering justice, into districts, to the chief town of each of which the proconsul or propraetor went from time to time to preside over the assize. To hold such an assize was styled agere conventus. Caesar generally used the winter months for this purpose; but his chief motive in going now into his Cisalpine province was probably that he might be nearer Rome, and so get better information of the political movements there.[A.U.C. 697.]BOOK II."

